    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-03-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Baker</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 8,
                            1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Nicaragua claims sovereignty over Mosquito Reservation; placed troops;
                        Bluefields declared martial law. Mosquito authorities protested; asked
                        protection British consul. English soldiers landed later. English and
                        Nicaraguan troops temporarily withdrawn. Referred to British minister,
                        Guatemala.</p>
            </div>
